  "text": "Let us mention that this two-step approach was used already in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] to count lattice walks confined in a quadrant. Then, we tried it successfully on vexillary involutions. Then, we tried it on all bi-labelled generating trees we could find in the world of patternavoiding permutations -and, to our surprise, the approach kept working, as is reported in this paper. A more recent example is provided by osculating walks [CITATION_3] . Needless to say, we would be interested in trying this method on other (combinatorially founded) trees with two labels: all examples are welcome!",
